## 10. Communication Codes

When a feature triggers notifications (email, push, SMS, WhatsApp), reference the exact communication code. The platform uses a standardized coding system for all communications.

### Format

Use the format **com[NNN]** (e.g. com234, com235, com243, com244). Always tag the communications owner when introducing a new code.

### Examples from Reference Stories

| Code | Trigger | Source |
|---|---|---|
| com234, com235 | Scan entry added to FST — triggered to participant | U210041 — Scan & Earn |
| com243 | Target allocation processed — triggered to distributors | U210090 — Type D Targets |
| com244 | Target allocation updated/overwritten — triggered for changed entries | U210090 — Type D Targets |

### Rules

- Every feature that triggers a notification must include the communication code in the AC.
- If a new code is needed, tag the communications owner inline.
- Distinguish between codes triggered on first action vs. codes triggered on subsequent updates.

---

## 11. Activity Codes and Permission Gating

Features gated by role-based permissions must reference the exact activity code.

### Format

Use the format **M[NNN]** (e.g. M105). State explicitly: (1) which activity code gates the feature, (2) which roles receive it, (3) what users without the activity see (hidden, greyed out, or error message).

### Example from U210041

> All sections Section 1, 2, 3, 4 will be available only with activity M105.
> M105 : Manage settings for Type G campaign.
> The above activity will be given to Product Admin only. For any user who does not have access to M105, will not even see campaign settings under Actions dropdown.

