## 12. Data Schema Documentation

When a feature creates a new system table (e.g. Base Scan Table, Target Table), document the schema as a table.

### 12.1 System Table Conventions

- **Table types:** System Table (auto-created by campaign, non-editable), Custom Data Table (admin-uploaded), Target Table (created by target distribution setup).
- **Naming:** Schema name is system-generated. Display name matches campaign name. Both visible to Campaign Owner / Client Admin / Report Owner / Product Admin. Never visible to participants.
- **Datasource exposure:** System tables are exposed in real-time under Datasources with Table Type = 'System Table'.
- **Allowed actions:** View (grid format) and Export Data only. No Edit, View Columns, Import Data, or Delete Table.

### 12.2 Example: Base Scan Table (BST) from U210041

| Column Name | Description | Data Source |
|---|---|---|
| Scan ID | Unique ID captured when someone scans | System generated |
| Scan Date | Date with timestamp when scan is captured | System generated |
| Scan Code | Code from uploaded/generated codes | SKU & Codes upload |
| SKU | SKU master value linked to code | Product hierarchy |
| User First/Last Name | User identity fields | User Table |
| User Dept / Desig / Role / Scope | User attributes | User Table |
| Scan Points | Base points assigned to SKU | Validation matrix |
| Incentive per scan | Used in Final Incentives Table | Calculation engine |
| Bonus per scan | Used in Final Incentives Table | Calculation engine |
| Scan Status | Success / Failed | Validation result |

### 12.3 Example: Target Table from U210090

| Column Name | Description | Data Source |
|---|---|---|
| Target ID | Primary column — system generated unique | System |
| User ID / Employee ID / Email / Mobile | Unique identifiers for the participant | User Table |
| Role / Scope / Dept / Designation | User attributes | User Table |
| Target Value | Numeric — defined through distribution process flow | Distribution |

