## 13. Widget & Variable Configuration Tables

When a feature involves configurable widgets or dashboard elements, document the full configuration matrix. This pattern is established in the Widgets_variables_MASTER_2025.xlsx reference file.

### 13.1 Widget Type Registry

| Code | Widget Title | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **A** | Status Card | Single status card for account details or verification (UPI, Bank, PAN verified) |
| **B** | Metric Card | Single variable card for KPI, sales, points or earnings. Supports Global, Campaign, or Data Sources metric source. |
| **C** | Progress Bar | Single progress bar for individual or team goal tracking |
| **D** | Campaign Card | Multi-variable card with 4–6 campaign variables |
| **E** | Text Card | Text card for greetings, dividers, or extra details |
| **F** | Quick Actions | Card with multiple shortcuts to key pages (Redeem, History, Support, Submit Bank/UPI/PAN, Hub) |
| **G** | Icon Card | (April 2026 sprint) |

### 13.2 Metric Card Configuration Steps

The Metric Card (Widget B) demonstrates the most complex multi-step configuration:

- **Step 1:** Widget title (free text)
- **Step 2:** Widget unit (free text, 6 char limit)
- **Step 3:** Unit as prefix / suffix (radio button)
- **Step 4:** Select metric source: Global / Campaign / Data Sources (radio button)

Then branch based on selection:

- **If Global:** Step 5 = dropdown (Earned / Redeemed / Expired / Balance / Earned from active / Redeemed from active / Balance from active)
- **If Campaign:** Step 5 = Select campaign, Step 6 = Select variable
- **If Data Sources:** Step 5 = Select table, Step 6 = Unique ID (data sources), Step 7 = Unique ID (user table), Step 8 = Select column

### 13.3 Click Destination Registry

Every clickable widget must document its click destination using the standard registry:

| Code | Category | Redirection Page | Short Form |
|---|---|---|---|
| a | Rewards | Total earned points detail page | Points |
| b | Rewards | Redeemed points detail page | Redeemed |
| c–d | Rewards | Expired / Balance points detail page | Expired / Balance |
| e–f | Rewards | Rewards page / My wallet transactions | Redeem / Wallet |
| g–i | Profile & KYC | Support / My profile / Tier | Get help / Profile / Tier |
| j–l | Profile & KYC | Submit Bank / Submit PAN / Submit UPI | Submit Bank/PAN/UPI |
| m–n | Campaign & Home | View campaign / View hub | Campaign / Documents |
| o | My Reportees | My reportees page | My team |

### 13.4 Required Admin Settings for Clickable Widgets

When writing user stories for widget configuration, ensure the admin can configure:

- **Widget Name** (text), **Widget Type** (dropdown), **KPI Source** (dropdown/search)
- **Visibility — Role** (multi-select), **Visibility — Campaign Type** (multi-select)
- **Mandatory Widget** (toggle), **Click Behaviour Type** (radio: Entire Card / Component)
- **Destination Type** (Modal / Side Panel / Page), **Destination Mapping** (dropdown/search)
- **Auto Variable Mapping** (toggle — pulls session params), **Manual Variable Override** (key-value)
- **Preview Click** (test destination in CMS)

