## 14. Reports Documentation Pattern

When a new campaign type or feature introduces reports, document:

- **Report name and whether new or existing**
- **Columns included** (reference BST/FST/User Table columns)
- **Hierarchy inclusion** — whether user hierarchy path is included and why/why not
- **Output format** — hierarchy selection + Excel-based reports tab vs. grid view
- **Analytics Dashboard impact** — always state explicitly, even if no structural changes required

---

## 15. Upload Template Documentation

When a feature involves file uploads, document:

- **Template name and download link label** (e.g. "Download Standard Template")
- **Version row** (Version | V1.0 as first row)
- **Column headers with data types and validation rules**
- **Sample data rows** with expected format (dates, codes, SKU references)
- **Success/Failure column** — system populates after processing
- **Error cases as a bullet list** ("SKU code not present, duplicate scan code, scan code exists in another campaign — #campaign_name#, past validity date")
- **Upload behaviour** — additive or full-replace, and what happens to existing data
- **Cross-reference to similar upload flows** ("Keep the upload process exactly similar to Approval Matrix Upload in Type B campaign")

