## 16. Final Review Checklist

**After completing the full user story, do a final pass to check for the following before submitting:**

| ✓ | Check |
|---|---|
| ☐ | No repetition across sections. Context & Problem Statement appears once. No separate Background, Goal, Core Pain Point, or Expected Outcomes sections that repeat the same information. |
| ☐ | AC numbering is continuous across all personas (no restarts). |
| ☐ | Every AC item is testable. No aspirational statements, no implementation instructions. |
| ☐ | AC that references an external file cites the exact filename. |
| ☐ | Error messages are written verbatim with [X]/[Y] placeholders defined. |
| ☐ | Communication codes (comNNN) included for any feature that triggers notifications. |
| ☐ | Activity codes (MNNN) included for any permission-gated feature, with role and fallback behaviour. |
| ☐ | Data schemas documented as tables, not prose. |
| ☐ | Edge cases are genuine edge cases, not restatements of the core flow. |
| ☐ | All examples and scenarios use realistic values from the actual feature spec — no fictional dropdown values or made-up data. |
| ☐ | No tool explainers, implementation instructions, or "What [Team] Needs to Do" sections. |
| ☐ | Open questions are tagged with @owner, not left as TBD. |
| ☐ | Cross-references to existing features are explicit ("similar to Type B distribution mechanism"). |
| ☐ | Metadata table is complete (version, date, author, sprint, dependency if applicable). |

